                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160214-110-off645 t18160214-110-crimeloc648"></join>. I lost my bacon on the 15th instant, between nine and ten at night.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160214-110-person1127">
                  MARY 
                  ANN WALKER
               <interp inst="t18160214-110-person1127" type="surname" value="ANN WALKER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160214-110-person1127" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160214-110-person1127" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the daughter. The prisoner was in the habit of coming into the shop, and asking for a halfpenny-worth of tobacco, which when I let him have, he would shuffle, and want bread instead of tobacco. He was in our shop on the night in question, and after he was gone, we missed the bacon; in consequence of some information, we went to the public-house close by, and there we found the bacon in the settle, with the prisoner; he then said to me that is your bacon.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160214-110-person1128">
